<p>POST to <code class="inline-code">/ondemand[TEST]/assignments/{transactionID}/tv/{viewId}</code></p>
<p>The body of the POST is JSON in the form:</p>
<pre class="wikicode prettyprint"><code>{
  &quot;data&quot;: {
    &quot;property&quot;: {
      &quot;stories&quot;: 3,
      &quot;pitch&quot;: &quot;7/12&quot;
    },
    &quot;fieldResource&quot;: {
      &quot;name&quot;: &quot;Josh Harden&quot;,
      &quot;type&quot;: &quot;Drone Pilot&quot;,
      &quot;payrollID&quot;: &quot;XYZ987&quot;
    }
  }
}
</code></pre>
<p>The <code class="inline-code">&quot;data&quot;</code> object should contain at least one value but doesn&#39;t need to contain all of the possible values, e.g. these are also valid:</p>
<pre class="wikicode prettyprint"><code>{
  &quot;data&quot;: {
    &quot;property&quot;: {
      &quot;stories&quot;: 5
    }
  }
}
</code></pre>
<pre class="wikicode prettyprint"><code>{
  &quot;data&quot;: {
    &quot;property&quot;: {
      &quot;pitch&quot;: &quot;2/12&quot;
    },
    &quot;fieldResource&quot;: {
      &quot;name&quot;: &quot;Patsy Hangdog&quot;,
      &quot;payrollID&quot;: &quot;ABC001&quot;
    }
  }
}
</code></pre>
<p>Valid viewId values are currently:</p>
<ul class="wiki-list0">
<li>SFI (carrier_id 3985225): <code class="inline-code">1339</code></li>
<li>Demo (carrier_id 2642910): <code class="inline-code">1563</code></li>
</ul>
<p>The call is processed and forwarded over to TrackVia immediately and will straightaway either return 200 Success or 400 error. When there&#39;s an error there&#39;ll be a JSON body of the form: <code class="inline-code">{&quot;error&quot;: &quot;invalid TV view ID&quot;}</code>.</p>
