<p>POST to /ondemand[TEST]/assignments/{transactionID}/setstatus</p>
<p>The body of the POST is JSON in this form:<br/>{<br/>&quot;status&quot;: &quot;Appointment Scheduled&quot;,<br/>&quot;datetime&quot;: &quot;2020-07-24T12:34:56Z&quot;,<br/>&quot;userId&quot;: &quot;cheywood&quot;<br/>}</p>
<p>The call is processed and forwarded over to Xact immediately and will straightaway either return 200 Success or 400 error. When there&#39;s an error there&#39;ll be a JSON body of this form: {&quot;error&quot;: &quot;invalid status&quot;}.</p>
<p>Valid statuses are:<br/>Job Started<br/>Job Completed<br/>Contacted<br/>Appointment Scheduled<br/>Appointment Cancelled<br/>Planned Inspection<br/>Inspected<br/>Not Sold<br/>Reviewed<br/>Rejected<br/>QA Rejected<br/>QA Approved<br/>Client Approved<br/>Client Rejected<br/>File Closed<br/>File Reopened</p>
<p>If a time zone is not specified with the datetime then it is presumed to be UTC.</p>
<p>The userid is required (and is not the same as an XactNet address).</p>
